//     Window Object : The window object represents an open window in a browser. It is browser's
//  object (not javascript) & is automatically created by browser. It is a global object with lots
// of properties & methods.

// DOM : When a browser pase is loaded, the browser creates a Document Object Model (DOM) of the page.
// Through DOM we can dynamically changes in html.
// ex-
// document.body.style.background = "red";
// document.body.childNodes[1].innerText = "abcd";

